SIMPLE: infusible
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infusible
<hw>In*fu"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Infuse</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>Capable of being
infused.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Doctrines being <qex>infusible</qex> into all.</q>
<rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infusible</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infusible
<hw>In*fu"si*ble</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
<ets>fusible</ets>: cf. F. <ets>infusible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not
fusible; incapable or difficult of fusion, or of being dissolved or
melted.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The best crucibles are made of Limoges earth, which seems
absolutely <qex>infusible</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Lavoisier (Trans.
).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infusibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
